==English==

===Etymology===
{{term|a-|lang=en}} + {{term|bio-|lang=en}} + {{term|genesis|lang=en}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌeɪˌbai.oʊˈdʒɛn.ə.sɪs/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|abiogeneses}}

# {{context|biology|lang=en}} The [[origination]] of living organisms from [[lifeless]] matter; such [[genesis]] as does not [[involve]] the action of living parents; [[spontaneous]] generation. {{defdate|Late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}} <ref>{{R:SOED5|page=4}}</ref>
#* {{quote-book|year=1870|author=Thomas Huxley|title=Imperial Granum, The Great Medicinal Food
|passage=I shall call the ... doctrine that living matter may be produced by not living matter, the hypothesis of '''abiogenesis'''}}

